.TH "snd_hdac_dsp_prepare" 9 "snd_hdac_dsp_prepare" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_hdac_dsp_prepare \- prepare for DSP loading
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" snd_hdac_dsp_prepare
.BI "(struct hdac_stream *azx_dev "  ","
.BI "unsigned int format "  ","
.BI "unsigned int byte_size "  ","
.BI "struct snd_dma_buffer *bufp "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "azx_dev" 12
HD-audio core stream used for DSP loading
.IP "format" 12
HD-audio stream format
.IP "byte_size" 12
data chunk byte size
.IP "bufp" 12
allocated buffer
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allocate the buffer for the given size and set up the given stream for
DSP loading.  Returns the stream tag (>= 0), or a negative error code.
